  "texts": [
    "Initially, the data paths for both groups were imported to identify the locations of the 60 academic essays.",
    "Then, the data were imported, and new filenames were assigned to each data group, with 'gpt' respesenting the GPT corpus and 'hmn' representing the L2 human corpus.",
    "The data for both corpora were reviewed to ensure successful importation.",
    "The next step involved cleaning all the data, conducted using the \"qyanteda\" package in R (Banks et al. 2018).",
    "This process assisted in converting all words in each text to lowercase, and numbers, functional words, prepositions (such as 'the', 'an', 'of', 'from'), pronouns (such as 'I', 'she', 'he'), and non-words (such as 'et al.'"
  ],
